title: BEDROOMS ON OPPOSITE SIDES * EXPOSED BIRCK * HIGH CEILINGS * HOT AREA!
posting_body: ['Well kept older pre war two bedroom on the East Williamsburg/Bushwick border.', 'Huge sunny bedrooms with great windows and closets on opposite sides of the apartment, Spacious living room/open kitchen features plenty of cabinets and stainless steel appliances.', 'Glossy oak hardwood floors throughout.', "Located just a few foot-steps to the Morgan and Jefferson L stops – you are right by Roberta's, El Cortez, Tutu's, Pine Box Rock Bar, 983 Funky Grill, and the list goes on…", "You'll love living in this lively, creative neighborhood surrounded by dozens of top-rated bars, restaurants, cafes, grocers, and music/art venues.", "Local favorites include Roberta's, Sweet Science, Honey's, Wayward Social, Syndicated, Guadalupe, Reclamation, Ichiran, Momo Sushi Shack, El Cortez.", "Short commute to Manhattan & easy access to the rest of Brooklyn's hottest neighborhoods.", 'Only 3 blocks from the L train at Morgan, 4 blocks from the Jefferson L and a 10-minute walk to the J, M trains at Flushing, just 20 minutes to Union Square!', '- You’ll be right around the corner from dozens of top-rated bars, restaurants, cafes, grocers, and music/art venues.', 'Local favorites include Mominette, Sea Wolf, Three Diamond Door, Precious Metal, The Rookery, Archie’s, Heavy Woods, Idlewild, Clara’s, Yours Sincerely, Chuko, Los Hermanos, Wheelhouse.', '1 months broker fee due at signing - showings by appointment only.', 'Text Leo: 917-808-0442']
